2. About initializing in Constructor:
Member initialization is allowed during declaration.
https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/data_members#Member_initialization
Is there any specific reason to move it to constructor?

There is no rules such as but It's better to initialise variable in constructor with other variable, and it's easy in future to find variable value, if class don't have constructor then it's fine to initialising inside class.
